    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-20T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-20T23:00:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860F.01/524: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé to the Czechoslovak Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-21T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 21, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2128. With reference to your 3, March 17, 5 p.m. Czecho, you may inform Ripka
                    that the desire of the Czechoslovak Government <pb facs="0529" n="517"
                        xml:id="pg_517"/> to enter into a civil affairs arrangement with this
                    Government is being taken under advisement, and we shall communicate with him at
                    a later time when it will be found appropriate to discuss the matter.</p>
                <p>Please so inform Phillips.<note n="1" xml:id="d456fn1">Presumably William
                        Phillips, Personal Representative of President Roosevelt.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
